ld diffusion. Finally, we are able to confirm the plausibility of\nthe temporal shifts by a simplistic random walk model.\n  The main conclusion to be drawn from this work is that the injection of\nmagnetic flux, coming from active regions as represented by sunspots, happens\non faster time scales than the removal of small-scale magnetic flux elements\nlater on.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 4 Oct 2017 16:16:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-12-20"}
