im$ 1.3 M$_{\\odot}$) with low-yield\n$^{56}$Ni or on a sub-Chandrasekhar-mass white dwarf ($\\sim$ 1.0 M$_{\\odot}$)\nmerging with a less massive white dwarf. This finding provides compelling\nevidence that one branch of the previously proposed explosion models, the\nhelium-ignition scenario, does exist in nature, and such a scenario may account\nfor explosions of white dwarfs in a wider mass range in contrast to what was\npreviously supposed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 4 Oct 2017 23:03:27 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-10-06"}
