(S_{ij}^a)$ and\n$\\mathbb E(S_{ij}^a)$ show that the bounds are sharp under a certain condition\nwe call MI-domination. Applications to concrete categories of transformations\nand partial transformations are given in Part II.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 5 Oct 2017 06:09:31 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 6 Oct 2017 09:19:52 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 10 Jan 2018 04:05:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-01-11"}
