\Phi_6$, $\\Phi_7$ or $\\Phi_{10}$. Theorem 4. If $G$ is the alternating group\n$A_n$, the Mathieu group $M_{11}$, $M_{12}$, the Janko group $J_1$ or the group\n$PSL_2(F_q)$, $SL_2(F_q)$, $PGL_2(F_q)$ (where $q$ is a prime power), then\n$H_[nr}^d(C(G),Q/Z)=0$ for any $d\\ge 2$. Besides the degree three unramified\ncohomology groups, we compute also the stable cohomology groups.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 5 Oct 2017 10:42:48 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 16 May 2018 02:41:13 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 24 Sep 2019 16:49:35 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-09-25"}
